IBM Corporation Opens Product Development Facility in Romania-SeeNews

Monday, 28 Nov 2011 07:00pm EST

SeeNews reported that IBM Corporation has opened in Romania its first European site for developing and testing IBM switch and networking hardware and software. The IBM Bucharest System Laboratory will leverage the Company’s 2010 acquisition of Blade Network Technologies and work to bulletproof IBM's products, such as IBM Networking Operation System and IBM VMready software. The 100-square-meter laboratory is located near another IBM facility, the IBM Business Analytics laboratory, in the capital Bucharest. It employs 125 engineers. Both facilities intend to work together to deliver solutions that are optimized to manage customers’ data growth. 

